review_blob: I love the labels on these beers! Pours a nice pale copper with orange hues. Very aromatic hops in this beer, smells of citrus peels and hints of pine. It has light carbonation on the palate and finishes a little dry. Tastes of bitter or tart fruits and again I get pine. The malts round out the flavor and make this beer an easy drinker. Overall I think this is a great IPA.

This beer pours a lovely golden yellow, with a light head. Little carbonation in this brew but a great earthy, yeasty breadlike aroma. It almost smells like sweet pastries. On the palate it is slighty sweet with these straw-like undertones. Overall I think its well balanced but lacking the overall body I wohl expect from a Saison.

Malty backbone balanced by the different hops. Dates and fig add a touch of sweetness but do not over power the beer. It pours a gorgeous auburn/amber color with a light head and medium body. Flavor is unique and distinctive, quite a tasty beer.
